  38,74,"but not Ibl√ģs,¬†who acted arrogantly,¬†becoming unfaithful"
  38,75,"God asked, ‚ÄúO Ibl√ģs! What prevented you from prostrating to what I created with My Own Hands? Did you ňĻjustňļ become proud? Or have you always been arrogant?‚ÄĚ"
  38,76,"He replied, ‚ÄúI am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.‚ÄĚ"
  38,77,"God commanded, ‚ÄúThen get out of Paradise, for you are truly cursed"
  38,78,And surely upon you is My condemnation until the Day of Judgment.‚ÄĚ
